#. type: Title ###
#: ../src/docs/labs/security/lab9-cryptography.md:781
#, no-wrap
msgid "Creating User Public and Private keys for SSH"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/labs/security/lab9-cryptography.md:784
#, no-wrap
msgid "Each individual user that wants to use SSH with RSA or DSA authentication needs a set of public keys and private keys. The ssh-keygen program can be used to create these keys ( just as it was used earlier when you created spare keys for your system)\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/labs/security/lab9-cryptography.md:786
#, no-wrap
msgid "The only “advised” difference when creating user keys is to also create a passphrase.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/labs/security/lab9-cryptography.md:788
#, no-wrap
msgid "The passphrase is a password that the is used to encrypt the private key before it is stored on the file system.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/labs/security/lab9-cryptography.md:790
#, no-wrap
msgid "The public is store in a file with the same file name as the private key but with the extension “.pub” appended to it. There is no way to recover a lost passphrase. If the passphrase is lost or forgotten, a new key must be generated.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/labs/security/lab9-cryptography.md:792
#, no-wrap
msgid "To create ying’s authentication keys\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '1. '
#: ../src/docs/labs/security/lab9-cryptography.md:794
#, no-wrap
msgid "Log into your local machine as the user ying.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '2. '
#: ../src/docs/labs/security/lab9-cryptography.md:796
#, no-wrap
msgid "Run the “ssh-keygen” program to create a “***dsa***” type key with the default length. Type:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/labs/security/lab9-cryptography.md:798
#, no-wrap
msgid "\\[ying@serverXY ying\\]$ ***ssh-keygen -t dsa***\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/labs/security/lab9-cryptography.md:800
#, no-wrap
msgid "Generating public/private dsa key pair.\n"
msgstr ""

